<TITLE> Bangladesh drawn with host Kyrgyzstan in AFC challenge Cup </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 16 (bdnews24.com) - Bangladesh have been placed in Group A along with hosts Kyrgyzstan, Afghanistan and Laos in the qualifying round of the AFC Challenge Cup. In this regard, a draw was held Wednesday at the AFC House in Kuala Lumpur. Sixteen teams, split into four groups, will play the group phase matches and the top nation from each group will join DPR Korea, Turkmenistan, hosts India and Myanmar in the eight-team finals, scheduled for July 30 to August 10. Apart from Kyrgyzstan, Chinese Taipei, Nepal and the Philippines will also host the qualifying round, schedules of which are yet to be finalised. The four qualifying groups will be hosted by Nepal, Kyrgyzstan, Chinese Taipei and the Philippines. Bangladesh hosted the inaugural AFC Challenge Cup in 2006 where Tajikistan emerged champions defeating Sri Lanka. Bangladesh quit the meet losing to Tajikistan 6-1 in the quarterfinals. Group A: Chinese Taipei (hosts), Sri Lanka, Pakistan and Guam Group B: The Philippines (hosts), Tajikistan, Brunei Darussalam and Bhutan Group C: Kyrgyzstan (hosts), Bangladesh, Afghanistan and Laos Group D: Nepal (hosts), Palestine, Cambodia and Macau. 
